<CMD> setViaGenMode -reset
<CMD> setViaGenMode -ignore_DRC 0 -allow_via_expansion 0 -extend_out_wire_end 1 -inherit_wire_status 1 -keep_existing_via 2 -partial_overlap_threshold 1 -allow_wire_shape_change 0 -keep_fixed_via 1 -optimize_cross_via 1 -disable_via_merging 1 -use_cce 1 -use_fgc 1
Setting -allow_via_expansion to 0. ViaGen will not allow via expanded outside of the intersection area.
Setting -allow_wire_shape_change to 0. ViaGen will not allow via to change the metal shape of existing wires.
Setting -disable_via_merging to 1. ViaGen disables via merging with the via created earlier.
Setting -extend_out_wire_end to 1. ViaGen will allow via extending outside of the end of the existing wires.
Setting -inherit_wire_status to 1. ViaGen will create vias and set the status as the bottom wires.
Setting -ignore_DRC to 0. ViaGen will do DRC check while creating vias.
Setting -keep_fixed_via to 1. Fixed vias cannot be modified by tool.
Setting -optimize_cross_via to 1. ViaGen will try to generate vias with the minimum enclosure.
Setting -use_cce to 1. ViaGen will call CCE to colorize via and may re-colorize surrounding vias to resolve color conflict within the local range.
